CANDLEMASS # NIGHTFALL # FULL ALBUM 1987

Nightfall is the second studio album from this Swedish doom metal legend. It was published on 9 November 1987. This album is considered the best metal album ever created Doom and best album of the band. The reason for this success is due in part to the new members who joined the band; Messiah Marcolin (vocals), Lars Johansson (lead guitar) and Jan Lindh (drums).

ORIGIN: STOCKHOLM, SWEDEN
GENRE: DOOM METAL
YEARS ACTIVE: 1984 - 1994, 1997 - 2002, 2004 - present
MEMBERS 1987:

Messiah Marcolin – Vocals
Lars Johansson – Lead guitar
Mats Björkman – Rhythm guitar
Leif Edling – Bass
Jan Lindh – Drums

description:
Official Video for “Leave Me Alone” by Michael Jackson
Listen to Michael Jackson: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_listenYD

Michael Jackson’s short film for “Leave Me Alone” is the seventh of nine short films for the “Bad” album.   The visually stunning  short film is the first of Michael’s songs and short films that serve as commentary on the media frenzy that often surrounded him and features a surreal amusement park built around a giant Michael tied down like Gulliver in the classic book Gulliver’s Travels. The short film won a Grammy Award for Best Short Form Music Video and was ranked one of the Top 10 Music Videos in a 2008 Rolling Stone critics’ poll.

Subscribe to the official Michael Jackson YouTube Channel: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/subscribeYD
title: Michael Jackson - Leave Me Alone (Official Video)
